3. Component Syntax
Simple Component
function Welcome() {
  return <h1>Hello React</h1>;
}
4. Line-by-Line Explanation
function Welcome() {
  return <h1>Hello React</h1>;
}
Line 1
function Welcome()

Creates a JavaScript function.

Important Rule

Component names must start with a capital letter.

✅ Correct

function Welcome()

❌ Wrong

function welcome()
Line 2
{

Function body starts.

Line 3
return

Returns JSX.

React displays whatever is returned.

Line 3
<h1>Hello React</h1>

JSX element.

Line 4
}

Function ends.

Using Component
function Welcome() {
  return <h1>Hello React</h1>;
}

export default function App() {
  return (
    <div>
      <Welcome />
    </div>
  );
}
