7. Nesting Components

Component inside another component.

Example:

function Header() {
  return <h1>Website Header</h1>;
}

function Footer() {
  return <h2>Website Footer</h2>;
}

export default function App() {
  return (
    <div>
      <Header />
      <Footer />
    </div>
  );
}
Visual Diagram
App
│
├── Header
│
└── Footer

React applications are built like trees.

App
│
├── Navbar
│
├── Hero
│
├── Services
│
└── Footer
8. Splitting Components into Files

As projects grow:

Don't put everything in one file.

Folder Structure
src
│
├── App.jsx
│
└── components
     │
     ├── Header.jsx
     ├── Footer.jsx
     └── Hero.jsx
Header.jsx
function Header() {
  return <h1>My Website</h1>;
}

export default Header;
App.jsx
import Header from "./components/Header";

function App() {
  return (
    <div>
      <Header />
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
